subdefinitions.definition: A city , unitary authority , and borough of Devon , England .
A sea area between Plymouth, Devon , England and France .
The mouth of the river Plym , in Devon , England .
The de jure and abandoned capital of Montserrat .
A small rural community of Pictou County , Nova Scotia , Canada .
A small rural community of Yarmouth County , Nova Scotia , Canada .

A number of places in the United States : A small city in Amador County , California . A town in Litchfield County , Connecticut . An unincorporated community in Orange County , Florida . A village in Hancock County and McDonough County , Illinois . A city , the county seat of Marshall County , Indiana . A minor city in Cerro Gordo County , Iowa . An unincorporated community in Lyon County , Kansas . A town in Penobscot County , Maine . A large town , one of the two county seats of Plymouth County , Massachusetts . A city in Wayne County , Michigan . A sizable city in Hennepin County , Minnesota ; a suburb of Minneapolis . A former settlement in Lowndes County , Mississippi . An unincorporated community in Carroll County , Missouri . A village in Jefferson County , Nebraska . A town in Grafton County , New Hampshire . A town in Chenango County , New York . A town , the county seat of Washington County , North Carolina . A village in Huron County and Richland County , Ohio . A borough of Luzerne County , Pennsylvania . A small town in Box Elder County , Utah . A small town in Windsor County , Vermont . An unincorporated community in Putnam County , West Virginia . A town in Juneau County , Wisconsin . A town in Rock County , Wisconsin . A town and city in Sheboygan County , Wisconsin . The Plymouth Colony , established by the Pilgrims . A number of townships in the United States , listed under Plymouth Township .
